Ukrainian Spring-Grain Planting Declines 13%, Ministry Says

-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 
2011-04-11T13:04:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/ukrainian-spring-grain-planting-declines-13-ministry-says.html
Ukrainian spring-grain planting
fell 13 percent from a year earlier to 2.3 million hectares (5.7
million acres) as of today, the Agriculture Ministry said.  Spring barley covered 1.73 million hectares, and spring
wheat was sown on 208,000 hectares, the Kiev-based ministry said
in an e-mailed statement.  Sugar-beet planting advanced 50 percent to 196,000
hectares, the ministry said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  